Functionalities{
                 -ASCII Graphics Display: The graphical interface is capable of displaying ASCII graphics, allowing the visual presentation of information.

                 -Operation Mode Selection: The user can select between different operation modes depending on the underlying program.

                 -Brightness Transitions: The interface offers brightness transitions using asterisks, adding a dynamic visual element.

                 -Screen Cleaning: You can clean the console screen to keep the interface clean and organized.

                 -Friendly Finishing: Before closing, the interface displays finishing messages for a more friendly user experience.
  }


Prerequisites{
                 -Windows Operating System: The interface is only compatible with Windows operating systems due to its dependency on the Windows.h library.

                 -C++ Compiler: A C++ compiler is required to compile the source code.
  }


Use{
                 -Mode Selection: Use the up and down arrow keys to toggle between the displayed operating modes. Press 'q' to confirm selection.

                 -Visualization: Observe the ASCII graphics and brightness transitions the interface offers for an enhanced visual experience.
  }

Code Structure{
  
                 -Libraries and Definitions: Inclusion of necessary libraries and definition of constants.

                 -Auxiliary Functions: Implementation of auxiliary functions to clear the screen, generate brightness transitions and display completion messages.

                 -ASCII graphics: Declaration of logos and ASCII graphics used by the interface.

                 -Main Function (main): Implementation of the main function that controls the flow of the interface, including selecting modes and calling the corresponding functions.
  }

